Call For Papers Workshop on Component- Based Software Engineering Process In conjunction with the Technology of Object- Oriented Languages and Systems ( TOOLS ) Conference ( http : / / www . tools . com / usa / ) Santa Barbara , Calif . , August 2 - 5 , 1999 Workshop Webpage - http : / / www . andromeda . rutgers . edu / ~ nwosu / tools 1999 / ) Over the years , it has been the ambition and goal of the Software Engineering committee to have the ability to quickly assemble or build a software system from compatible and cooperating entities or components . At last , the long cherished ambition of Software System Developers and Integrators is coming to fruition . This has been largely motivated by similar abilities in the companion hardware areas and also by the other foreseeable by products such as shortened time to market and increased productivity . The Component- Based Software Engineering ( CBSE ) process departs drastically from the conventional software development process in that it ? s integration-centric as opposed to development-centric . And a true CBSE depends mostly on selection , acquisition , and integration of components from external vendors , which raises a lot of issues and problems . There are numerous issues , questions , and risks involved in component selection , acquisition , and integration that must be adequately addressed and resolved in a CBSE project . And all these , and other necessary tasks , such as requirements engineering , domain engineering , etc . , must be addressed in the context of a formal Component- Based Software System Development ( CBSE ) Process . Workshop Scope : The goal of this workshop is to address issues involved and surrounding the development of Component- Based Software System Development ( CBSE ) processes . As a result , this workshop will target research and industrial works and experiences that deal with the following issues as they related to CBSE processes : - requirements engineering and analysis - domain engineering and analysis - interface specification languages and tools - component evaluation - testing & integration - modeling - design and development - risk analysis and management - process models - system frameworks and architectures - system maintenance - repository management Paper Submission : Authors are invited to electronically submit original research and / or experience reports in English . Abstracts should not be longer than 2 double-spaced pages and full-papers should not be longer than 20 double-spaced pages . Each submission should include each author 's full name , affiliation , complete address , telephone number , Internet address , and , if available , FAX number . Notification and reviews will be conducted and communicated electronically . Submitters should indicate , during paper submission , their willingness to attend the workshop and present their paper . All paper submissions will be done via the Web via http : / / www . andromeda . rutgers . edu / ~ nwosu / tools 1999 / submit / Submitted papers are refereed by at least three reviewers from the workshop Program Committee for quality , correctness , originality , and relevance . Accepted papers will be presented at the workshop and included in the TOOLS conference proceedings . Important Dates : Paper submission ( Abstract or full paper ) : April 15 , 1999 . Notification of acceptance : April 29 , 1999 Camera-ready copy due : May 14 , 1999 .
